1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:08,008
["Lady Luck" by Richard Swift playing]

2
00:00:12,178 --> 00:00:14,014
[woman] This is Paxton Hall-Yoshida.

3
00:00:14,097 --> 00:00:16,975
He's a 16-year-old boy
from Sherman Oaks, California,

4
00:00:17,058 --> 00:00:20,270
and I am model, designer, activist,

5
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:23,398
and a former 16-year-old from California,
Gigi Hadid.

6
00:00:23,481 --> 00:00:24,524
[cameras clicking]

7
00:00:24,607 --> 00:00:25,984
[reporters clamoring]

8
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:26,943
[inaudible]

9
00:00:28,778 --> 00:00:30,196
You may be asking yourself,

10
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:32,824
"Why is Old Gigers
taking time out of her busy skedge

11
00:00:32,907 --> 00:00:35,076
to narrate the story
of a 16-year-old boy?"

12
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:37,829
-[phone vibrating]
-Believe it or not, I relate to this kid.

13
00:00:37,912 --> 00:00:41,833
We're both constantly underestimated
because people only see us as sex symbols.

14
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:44,711
♪ She would find some time
To spend with me ♪

15
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:49,841
[Hadid] When scientists declare your face
to be perfectly symmetrical,

16
00:00:49,924 --> 00:00:52,510
that's all everyone thinks
you have to offer the world,

17
00:00:52,594 --> 00:00:56,097
but we've got brains, too,
and feelings, and…

18
00:00:56,181 --> 00:00:59,267
Paxton, dude, put a shirt on!
I'm trying to make a point here.

19
00:01:00,643 --> 00:01:03,104
Anyway, we have
so much more going on inside.

20
00:01:03,813 --> 00:01:06,983
At least that's true for me.
We'll see what happens with Paxton.

21
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:09,069
[music continues]

22
00:01:10,945 --> 00:01:14,115
♪ Lady luck, she is lovely ♪

23
00:01:16,284 --> 00:01:19,037
[groans] Dude, my arm. What the hell?

24
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:21,372
I just wanted to make sure
you're not faking it.

25
00:01:21,456 --> 00:01:23,583
Wow, you're, like, really hurt, bruh.

26
00:01:23,666 --> 00:01:26,920
[Hadid] Uh, yeah, he was like,
"really hurt, bruh,"

27
00:01:27,003 --> 00:01:30,298
but it wasn't just his arm,
and it was all this chick's fault.

28
00:01:30,381 --> 00:01:31,800
[bell ringing]

29
00:01:31,883 --> 00:01:34,469
Ever since Devi came into Paxton's life,

30
00:01:34,552 --> 00:01:37,180
it's been nothing but chaos and confusion.

31
00:01:39,182 --> 00:01:41,935
[softly] Paxton, I am so sorry.

32
00:01:42,018 --> 00:01:44,771
It's just so weird
seeing you all busted up.

33
00:01:44,854 --> 00:01:46,356
I'm still prettier than you are.

34
00:01:46,439 --> 00:01:50,151
Hey, I have a vibrant countenance
that people find relatable and appealing.

35
00:01:50,235 --> 00:01:52,320
[Hadid] Paxton wasn't
really the jealous type,

36
00:01:52,403 --> 00:01:55,365
but the fact that Devi,
the weirdest girl he'd ever liked,

37
00:01:55,448 --> 00:01:59,035
was two-timing him with Ben Gross
really screwed with his head.

38
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:02,664
I mean Ben Gross, really?

39
00:02:04,249 --> 00:02:06,501
♪ 'Cause I just got that feeling ♪

40
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:09,796
♪ If I can be better ♪

41
00:02:09,879 --> 00:02:12,382
[Hadid] What did Ben Gross have
that Paxton didn't?

42
00:02:12,465 --> 00:02:13,967
Besides a screening room and a--

43
00:02:14,050 --> 00:02:18,263
Whoa, is that a Patek Philippe watch?
Damn, I don't even have one of those.

44
00:02:18,346 --> 00:02:20,515
I have some unpleasant news.

45
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:23,184
According to the powers that be,

46
00:02:23,268 --> 00:02:26,312
I am no longer allowed to test you guys

47
00:02:26,396 --> 00:02:29,023
on your feelings about history.

48
00:02:29,107 --> 00:02:32,110
Apparently, they think it's more valuable

49
00:02:32,193 --> 00:02:35,029
for you to know about things like dates,

50
00:02:35,113 --> 00:02:36,698
and facts,

51
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:38,867
and the names of dead white men.

52
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:41,661
So, is the test gonna multiple choice, or…

53
00:02:41,744 --> 00:02:44,831
[scoffs] Multiple choice.
Yeah, you'd love that, wouldn't you?

54
00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:48,918
Can we choose two answers for a question,
or do we have to commit to just one?

55
00:02:49,002 --> 00:02:53,298
Interesting, Ben. I am definitely open
to there being multiple answers.

56
00:02:53,381 --> 00:02:56,134
No, there should only be one choice,

57
00:02:57,135 --> 00:02:59,179
and Devi should have known what it was.

58
00:02:59,262 --> 00:03:01,639
[somber music playing]

59
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:07,103
[Marcus] Can't believe
you got played by dorks.

60
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:10,481
Are you not as hot as you used to be?
Am I the hottest one in the group now?

61
00:03:10,565 --> 00:03:15,195
Yeah, Coyote Girl cheated on you
with that Young Sheldon-looking dude,

62
00:03:15,278 --> 00:03:18,323
and now you smell like wet cast.
You've lost your edge, man.

63
00:03:18,406 --> 00:03:20,950
Shut up, dickhead.
I haven't lost anything.

64
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:23,203
Anyone want to sign my cast?

65
00:03:24,037 --> 00:03:26,456
[Hadid] Paxton had no shortage
of female admirers.

66
00:03:26,539 --> 00:03:29,375
Legend has it,
he romanced Kaia Gerber at summer camp

67
00:03:29,459 --> 00:03:31,294
when he was just a boy of ten.

68
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:36,466
See? The only mistake I made was letting
crazy Devi drag me into her psychodrama.

69
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:38,384
[laughs] "Crazy Devi"?

70
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:41,137
Oh my God, that is so good. She is crazy.

71
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:43,389
Remember when she fell in that guy's pool?

72
00:03:43,473 --> 00:03:46,309
That guy? You mean Ben, your ex-boyfriend?

73
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:48,478
Oh, right! I forgot about him!

74
00:03:49,103 --> 00:03:51,648
"Crazy Devi." That's hilare. [laughs]

75
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:53,524
[Zoe] Remember when she had
that weird party?

76
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:55,193
And that guy fell off the roof?

77
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:56,903
[laughs] That was me.

78
00:03:56,986 --> 00:03:58,071
[laughs]

79
00:03:58,154 --> 00:04:01,282
[Hadid] As a champion swimmer,
Paxton had never worried about college.

80
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:03,993
He'd already been courted
by some pretty dope schools

81
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:05,620
like Stanford and UCLA.

82
00:04:05,703 --> 00:04:06,788
So he thought it was weird

83
00:04:06,871 --> 00:04:09,457
when the college counselor
suddenly asked to see him.

84
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:12,210
Good afternoon, Paxton.
Thank you for meeting with me.

85
00:04:12,293 --> 00:04:15,171
No problem.
I didn't even know this room was here.

86
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:18,132
Let me cut to the chase.
I spoke to your coach this morning,

87
00:04:18,216 --> 00:04:20,635
and due to the severity of your injury,

88
00:04:20,718 --> 00:04:24,514
you might have to face the possibility
that you might not swim for Stanford.

89
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:27,600
Well, I'd still be cool
with going to Stanford,

90
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:29,143
even if I can't swim there.

91
00:04:29,227 --> 00:04:30,895
-[Hadid] Oh, sweetie…
-[chuckles]

92
00:04:30,979 --> 00:04:33,690
I think we need to cast a wider net.

93
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:37,235
You see, what you have
are college athlete grades,

94
00:04:37,318 --> 00:04:42,615
and when you subtract the athlete part,
your options tend to narrow.

95
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:44,617
Wait, so where can I get in?

96
00:04:45,118 --> 00:04:48,454
I'm fine with anything as long as it's,
you know, close to a beach,

97
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:51,124
has a good basketball team,
the classes aren't too hard,

98
00:04:51,207 --> 00:04:53,835
but like some smart people still go there.

99
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:56,879
Ah-ha. Well, let's see.

100
00:04:57,797 --> 00:05:00,216
First off,
are your parents extremely wealthy?

101
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:02,677
-No.
-All right.

102
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:07,015
In that case, perhaps a two-year
or community college might be a safer bet.

103
00:05:08,766 --> 00:05:10,560
Look, we can shoot higher,

104
00:05:10,643 --> 00:05:14,188
but you'll need to significantly
improve your GPA.

105
00:05:14,772 --> 00:05:16,607
Would you be open to being tutored?

106
00:05:16,691 --> 00:05:18,609
Um… I guess.

107
00:05:18,693 --> 00:05:21,863
Great! Because I took the liberty
of setting you up

108
00:05:21,946 --> 00:05:25,241
with the best peer tutor
in the entire school.

109
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:28,244
[laughs] This girl is an academic beast.

110
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:29,829
-[laughs quietly]
-[knocking on door]

111
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:31,873
[Devi] Uh…

112
00:05:31,956 --> 00:05:34,709
Sorry, she didn't tell me it was you.

113
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:37,378
Oh, you two know each other? [gasps]

114
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:38,880
Oh, no. Let me guess.

115
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:43,092
She was some sort of bet
with your cool friends.

116
00:05:43,217 --> 00:05:44,719
What? No.

117
00:05:45,386 --> 00:05:47,722
I'd rather not go to college
than work with her.

118
00:05:53,978 --> 00:05:56,481
Hey, what are you doing home so early?

119
00:05:56,564 --> 00:05:59,859
Oh, right. No swimming for you, Nemo.

120
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:02,487
Yeah, no swimming for me.

121
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:03,654
[door closes]

122
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:07,950
Wait, do you usually come hang out
at my house when I'm not home?

123
00:06:08,534 --> 00:06:11,704
Yep. I find it's a peaceful place to sit
with my thoughts,

124
00:06:11,788 --> 00:06:13,122
or to watch porn.

125
00:06:14,165 --> 00:06:17,502
-Didn't need to know that.
-What's wrong, buddy? You seem down.

126
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:22,006
Ms. Warner said that without swimming,
college isn't looking too great for me.

127
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:24,008
Eh, who needs college?

128
00:06:24,092 --> 00:06:26,511
After high school,
I'm going straight to YouTube.

129
00:06:26,594 --> 00:06:30,765
Get this.
I'm gonna react to reaction videos.

130
00:06:30,848 --> 00:06:32,642
[Hadid] Yikes.

131
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:34,560
-Cool.
-I know, right? [chuckles]

132
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:37,313
Paxton, you good?

133
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:40,149
Yeah. Yeah, I'm… I'm great, man.

134
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:41,109
I just

135
00:06:41,818 --> 00:06:44,278
kinda don't know
what I'm doing with myself.

136
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:46,572
I'll tell you what your doing.
You're hanging out with me.

137
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:49,367
Now that you're free,
we can party every day.

138
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,539
You wanna blow some shit up?

139
00:06:55,164 --> 00:06:57,375
Oh shit. [laughs]

140
00:06:57,458 --> 00:06:58,334
[rock music playing]

141
00:06:58,418 --> 00:06:59,252
-[explodes]
-Oh!

142
00:06:59,335 --> 00:07:00,169
Oh, yeah!

143
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:03,381
-[explodes]
-[both] Oh!

144
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:06,884
-[explodes]
-Oh! [laughs]

145
00:07:06,968 --> 00:07:09,178
Watch the screen and you'll know, Shira.

146
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:10,888
-[explodes]
-Oh yeah!

147
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:13,433
-I told you. I told you. [laughs]
-Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

148
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:15,351
I'm pushing A and the left joystick.

149
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:18,312
You're not supposed to click A,
and you're not doing it.

150
00:07:18,396 --> 00:07:19,856
You're not moving the left joystick.

151
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:21,149
[groans]

152
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:23,609
Wow, dude,
that reaction was kind of weird.

153
00:07:23,693 --> 00:07:25,695
[laughing]

154
00:07:25,778 --> 00:07:27,447
Yo, that reaction was good.

155
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:29,031
That was sick!

156
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:30,950
Dude, that's a surprising reaction.

157
00:07:31,033 --> 00:07:31,993
[yells]

158
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:34,203
[laughs]

159
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:35,872
He left. [laughs]

160
00:07:36,831 --> 00:07:39,250
Nice. Really descriptive, bro.

161
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:40,168
[exhales]

162
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:44,714
Your reaction to my reaction
to their reaction just made my life, bruh.

163
00:07:44,797 --> 00:07:46,090
[grunts]

164
00:07:48,885 --> 00:07:50,470
This week has been the best.

165
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:53,681
And you know what next week
is gonna be like? Exactly the same.

166
00:07:53,764 --> 00:07:56,851
-[opens can]
-For the rest of our lives, baby!

167
00:07:56,934 --> 00:07:57,894
[chuckles]

168
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:00,021
For the rest of our lives.

169
00:08:00,104 --> 00:08:01,898
[solemn music playing]

170
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:06,611
-Huh?
-I need you

171
00:08:07,778 --> 00:08:09,447
to help me get into college.

172
00:08:10,072 --> 00:08:12,074
[school bell ringing]

173
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:15,828
All right. This doesn't have to be weird.
We can be study buddies.

174
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:18,956
Could I offer you a soda,
or a water, or a hot tea?

175
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:22,210
Cool. Cool, cool, cool.

176
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:24,962
I actually work a little better, too,
when I'm dehydrated.

177
00:08:26,756 --> 00:08:29,592
Oh. Wow.
This book has not been opened before.

178
00:08:31,552 --> 00:08:36,140
-So where should we start? Math?
-You mean where should you start?

179
00:08:36,807 --> 00:08:41,270
Look, when I said I needed your help,
I meant I need you to do my work for me.

180
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:44,148
So, when you're done
with my English essay, you can start--

181
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:47,443
What? I can't do that.
That would be cheating.

182
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,862
Cool.
Then you should be really good at it, huh?

183
00:08:50,696 --> 00:08:53,199
-Paxton, let me explain.
-Explain what?

184
00:08:53,741 --> 00:08:56,285
How you thought you could get away
with dating both of us?

185
00:08:56,827 --> 00:08:59,247
[scoffs] You must think I'm such an idiot.

186
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:00,790
I don't think you're an idiot.

187
00:09:00,873 --> 00:09:03,501
I liked you. You know, I thought we were…

188
00:09:04,710 --> 00:09:05,545
What?

189
00:09:06,921 --> 00:09:07,755
Doesn't matter.

190
00:09:08,422 --> 00:09:10,925
Paxton. I'm really, really sorry.

191
00:09:11,008 --> 00:09:14,720
Look, I could honestly give a shit
about you and Ben Gross. All right?

192
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:17,682
But you trashed my chances
at a swimming scholarship.

193
00:09:18,182 --> 00:09:21,602
So now I'm going to college
on a you-doing-my-homework scholarship.

194
00:09:22,228 --> 00:09:23,104
We good?

195
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:26,148
Cool.

196
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:27,650
[somber music playing]

197
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:30,069
[door opens, closes]

198
00:09:30,152 --> 00:09:31,696
[video game beeping]

199
00:09:37,034 --> 00:09:39,996
Sorry to interrupt, but I did your math
and your English essay,

200
00:09:40,079 --> 00:09:43,291
and I made this serving dish
for your art class.

201
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:46,669
I think it's a rustic conversation piece
for any elegant tablescape--

202
00:09:46,752 --> 00:09:48,546
Cool. You can just leave it right there.

203
00:09:49,380 --> 00:09:51,757
[Hadid] I mean,
what Devi did to Paxton was cruel,

204
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:53,676
but this is straight-up humiliating.

205
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:56,220
Yo, you're blocking the screen!

206
00:09:56,304 --> 00:09:59,307
Damn, Crazy Devi,
you made me 'splode myself.

207
00:09:59,932 --> 00:10:02,059
[Hadid] And Paxton wasn't enjoying
punishing her

208
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:03,728
as much as he thought he would.

209
00:10:05,521 --> 00:10:07,857
I can't believe you said that to her face.

210
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:10,610
-[laughing]
-She was literally blocking the screen.

211
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:15,531
[Hadid] Even getting his very first "A"
felt like a pretty hollow victory.

212
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:17,325
It's like when you see
an overly photoshopped

213
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:18,993
swimsuit photo of yourself.

214
00:10:19,076 --> 00:10:22,455
Your butt may look right and tight,
but you know you didn't earn it.

215
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:26,334
-[laughs]
-[footsteps approaching]

216
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:31,172
Okay, so I need you to do the unit six
questions in my biology textbook,

217
00:10:31,255 --> 00:10:34,467
and here is a Spanish take home quiz
on parts of the body.

218
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:35,760
I already filled in…

219
00:10:35,843 --> 00:10:37,011
[in Spanish] Eggs.

220
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:40,931
Bueno. Muchísimas gracias. Adiós.

221
00:10:41,015 --> 00:10:41,932
What?

222
00:10:42,892 --> 00:10:44,477
I'll get these to you tomorrow.

223
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:45,519
Oh.

224
00:10:46,145 --> 00:10:48,689
Oh. Hey, Rebecca. Cool fit as always.

225
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:50,691
-Thanks, Devi.
-[Devi] See ya.

226
00:10:53,194 --> 00:10:55,071
You're making Devi do your homework?

227
00:10:55,905 --> 00:10:57,365
Keep it down, please?

228
00:10:57,448 --> 00:10:58,949
Look, I can explain.

229
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:00,701
She's the reason I don't have--

230
00:11:00,785 --> 00:11:01,619
Any dignity?

231
00:11:02,244 --> 00:11:04,747
No. Ouch. Jesus, Rebecca.

232
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:07,667
She's the reason I don't have a chance
at a scholarship anymore.

233
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:09,877
It makes sense for her to help me.
She owes me.

234
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:10,961
No one owes you.

235
00:11:11,045 --> 00:11:13,714
I had to work so hard
to get into my fashion program.

236
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:18,386
-I know. All right, and I'm proud of you.
-Don't you want to be proud of yourself?

237
00:11:18,469 --> 00:11:20,971
I just want to go to college. Period.

238
00:11:21,055 --> 00:11:24,266
And without Devi,
I don't know if I can make that happen.

239
00:11:24,892 --> 00:11:26,894
Then maybe you don't deserve to go.

240
00:11:27,603 --> 00:11:30,690
[Hadid] Damn, Rebecca. Drag his ass.

241
00:11:30,773 --> 00:11:33,192
Not that I'm taking sides.
I am his narrator.

242
00:11:34,193 --> 00:11:37,905
♪ And now let the weak
Say they are strong ♪

243
00:11:37,988 --> 00:11:40,658
[Hadid] Paxton's parents,
Kevin and June Hall-Yoshida,

244
00:11:40,741 --> 00:11:42,451
ran a local sporting goods store,

245
00:11:42,535 --> 00:11:45,079
and as you can see here,
were a little Jesus-y,

246
00:11:45,162 --> 00:11:46,288
but in a chill way.

247
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:50,626
Like in a "we've got one of those
fun fish stickers on our Volkswagen" way.

248
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:54,004
Amen. So, Paxton, Ojichan called.

249
00:11:54,088 --> 00:11:56,340
Uh, he said, "Email is broken."

250
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:59,885
So could you go by after school
and help him out? He loves seeing you.

251
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:03,180
Sure. It's not like
I have anything else going on.

252
00:12:04,223 --> 00:12:05,975
So how's everything at school?

253
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:06,976
[sighs]

254
00:12:07,059 --> 00:12:08,936
Yeah, your college counselor called,

255
00:12:09,019 --> 00:12:11,564
and she said now that swimming's
on the back burner--

256
00:12:11,647 --> 00:12:13,899
-I have to raise my grades.
-Yeah.

257
00:12:13,983 --> 00:12:15,651
I know. I got it covered.

258
00:12:15,735 --> 00:12:17,361
Someone's got it covered.

259
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:19,530
But, honey, to be honest,

260
00:12:19,613 --> 00:12:22,491
I told Mrs. Warner that I'm not gonna put
that kind of pressure on you.

261
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:25,578
Our family values kindness
over achievement.

262
00:12:25,661 --> 00:12:26,829
Yeah.

263
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:31,625
-You don't think I can get into college?
-No, honey. That's not what we meant.

264
00:12:32,877 --> 00:12:34,837
Just school's never been your thing.

265
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:38,382
Yeah, and we want you to know
that if you don't go to college,

266
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:40,301
that is totally okay.

267
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:42,970
You know, just hang back.
Work at the store with me.

268
00:12:43,053 --> 00:12:46,432
Yeah, and we always sell
so many sports bras during your shifts.

269
00:12:46,515 --> 00:12:48,267
[Hadid] Whoa, these hippie Christians

270
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:50,686
have some real low expectations
for their kid.

271
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:53,189
Like, lower than Paxton's dad's ponytail.

272
00:12:53,272 --> 00:12:56,233
Have you guys ever thought
that maybe I want to go to college?

273
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:58,152
-You do?
-Of course.

274
00:12:58,861 --> 00:13:01,322
I want an education, a career.

275
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:04,825
Well, that's really cool, sweetheart,

276
00:13:04,909 --> 00:13:08,287
but if you wanna go to college,
you're gonna have to work really hard.

277
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:11,791
I can work hard.
Why don't you think I can work hard?

278
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:13,292
I'd like to answer that.

279
00:13:13,375 --> 00:13:15,586
No, please don't.

280
00:13:16,462 --> 00:13:19,465
[Hadid] It was bad enough
his peers and teachers underestimated him,

281
00:13:19,548 --> 00:13:23,135
but hearing his parents excuse him
from even trying to go to college

282
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:24,720
really cut Paxton to the core.

283
00:13:25,846 --> 00:13:29,308
-What do you want your new password to be?
-Um, uh, dog.

284
00:13:29,391 --> 00:13:30,601
That's too short.

285
00:13:30,684 --> 00:13:33,687
-Okay, dogs.
-It needs to be at least eight letters.

286
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:36,607
Oh, man, that's too many letters. I'm old.

287
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:37,858
-[laughs]
-[knock on door]

288
00:13:37,942 --> 00:13:38,776
Yeah?

289
00:13:39,777 --> 00:13:43,364
Ted, how about some fresh lemonade?

290
00:13:43,447 --> 00:13:46,075
[laughs] Cheryl,
this is my grandson, Paxton.

291
00:13:46,158 --> 00:13:50,871
Oh. So handsome.
Just like his grandfather.

292
00:13:50,955 --> 00:13:52,206
-Ah.
-[Cheryl chuckles]

293
00:13:52,748 --> 00:13:54,750
I'll come back when you're alone.

294
00:13:54,834 --> 00:13:55,709
[laughs]

295
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:57,711
-[door closes]
-Damn, player.

296
00:13:57,795 --> 00:14:01,423
Well, look who's talking.
I noticed all those hearts on the cast.

297
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:03,259
Yeah, you know. I get it from you.

298
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:05,010
-[chuckles]
-Yeah. [laughs]

299
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:08,806
-Hey, Ojichan?
-Yeah?

300
00:14:08,889 --> 00:14:10,474
-Can I ask you something?
-Sure.

301
00:14:11,475 --> 00:14:14,353
Do you think I'm too stupid
to go to college?

302
00:14:14,979 --> 00:14:17,273
What? Who told you that?

303
00:14:18,065 --> 00:14:21,110
Basically everyone, including my parents.

304
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:22,444
Oh, what do they know?

305
00:14:22,528 --> 00:14:25,239
Look, don't get me wrong.
I mean, I love them,

306
00:14:25,322 --> 00:14:27,992
but they spend too much time in the sun.
It cooks their brains.

307
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:30,953
-[laughs]
-You are smart enough to go to college.

308
00:14:31,036 --> 00:14:34,331
You were fluent in Japanese
by the time you were five.

309
00:14:34,415 --> 00:14:35,916
[in Japanese] I think you are a genius.

310
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:38,919
-Arigato, Ojichan.
-Mmm.

311
00:14:39,003 --> 00:14:42,715
Paxton, people are going to think
all sorts of things about you.

312
00:14:43,507 --> 00:14:45,926
That you're not smart,
that you don't belong,

313
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:49,013
that you're the handsomest man
in the whole assisted living center.

314
00:14:49,096 --> 00:14:50,681
-[knock on door]
-Yeah?

315
00:14:50,764 --> 00:14:52,933
[woman] Oh, Ted. I made you a chicken.

316
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:54,602
I'm busy, Gladys!

317
00:14:55,227 --> 00:14:56,145
[laughs]

318
00:14:56,228 --> 00:15:00,482
But, Paxton, the only opinion of you
that truly matters is yourself.

319
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:03,235
So make yourself proud. Okay?

320
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:08,490
Now, I want to give this to you. Here.

321
00:15:09,033 --> 00:15:12,453
You try and give this to me every time.
It's a box of books you don't want.

322
00:15:12,536 --> 00:15:15,956
No, they're family heirlooms.
Some of them are very old.

323
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:16,957
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

324
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:20,169
Because this is the novelization
of Avatar.

325
00:15:20,252 --> 00:15:23,213
And you will cherish it
when I'm dead and gone,

326
00:15:23,297 --> 00:15:26,842
and you will pass on the wisdom
of the Na'vi to your grandchildren.

327
00:15:28,218 --> 00:15:30,554
-Thank you. [chuckles]
-Now, how about some chicken?

328
00:15:31,722 --> 00:15:32,806
[school bell ringing]

329
