Hey, are you okay? What happened?

422
00:20:22,262 --> 00:20:25,224
I don't know. It was the craziest thing.

423
00:20:25,307 --> 00:20:28,852
My… My heart was racing,
and I felt like I couldn't breathe.

424
00:20:28,936 --> 00:20:33,190
[sighs] I mean, all over a history test.
What's wrong with me?

425
00:20:34,942 --> 00:20:36,902
I think you had a little panic attack.

426
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:39,696
I… I used to get nervous
before swim meets,

427
00:20:39,780 --> 00:20:42,991
but, I mean, once I hit the water,
it went away

428
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:44,785
because I knew I was good at it.

429
00:20:44,868 --> 00:20:48,205
Well, you can be good at school too.
You just need to practice.

430
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:50,832
Were you good at the butterfly
the first time you tried it?

431
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:53,168
Yeah. I set a school record.

432
00:20:53,961 --> 00:20:57,172
Oh. Wow.
That's famously a very hard stroke.

433
00:20:57,798 --> 00:21:00,592
-Not for me.
-Okay, Michael Phelps. Chill.

434
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:02,719
But back to the school thing.

435
00:21:02,803 --> 00:21:04,930
I think it's good
