436
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:08,600
Why? It felt awful.

437
00:21:08,684 --> 00:21:11,144
Well, it means you care.

438
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:13,563
You care about school.

439
00:21:15,065 --> 00:21:18,110
Oh, damn. I guess I do.

440
00:21:18,902 --> 00:21:20,028
Weird.

441
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:23,198
[scoffs] It's not like
it really helped me much.

442
00:21:23,282 --> 00:21:27,160
I definitely failed that test. I mean,
I think I even got today's date wrong.

443
00:21:27,244 --> 00:21:30,497
Well, it's a good thing
you have a pushy Indian mother.

444
00:21:30,580 --> 00:21:32,791
Get up. Let's go.
I want to talk to your teacher.

445
00:21:32,874 --> 00:21:35,127
-Are you deaf? Get up! Let's go!
-[bell ringing]

446
00:21:35,210 --> 00:21:37,004
-Okay. Okay.
-Let's go. Now.

447
00:21:37,087 --> 00:21:38,171
All right. Okay.

448
00:21:41,049 --> 00:21:43,969
Mr. Shapiro,
Paxton would like to retake his test.

449
00:21:44,553 --> 00:21:49,474
I'm sorry, guys. That wouldn't be fair
to the other students.

450
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:53,770
Mr. Shapiro, because you bowed
to the establishment,

451
00:21:53,854 --> 00:21:56,273
Paxton was besieged
by a crisis of self-worth.

452
00:21:56,898 --> 00:22:00,902
If you don't give him a second chance,
you're teaching him that it is not okay

453
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:02,487
