Thanks for pushing me, by the way.

479
00:23:16,103 --> 00:23:20,690
Of course. I mean, I sort of owe you
for the fact that you got hit by a car.

480
00:23:22,943 --> 00:23:24,694
And the other thing.

481
00:23:25,529 --> 00:23:27,531
Yeah, the other thing.

482
00:23:27,614 --> 00:23:30,283
We really don't need to talk about that.

483
00:23:31,535 --> 00:23:32,369
We're cool.

484
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:36,206
Really? Wow. That's a relief.

485
00:23:36,289 --> 00:23:37,124
Yeah.

486
00:23:37,999 --> 00:23:41,420
I mean, it's… it's crazy when you think
about it, right? You and me?

487
00:23:42,421 --> 00:23:44,881
I mean, there's no way
it would've worked out.

488
00:23:45,924 --> 00:23:49,678
I mean,
we just don't make any sense, you know?

489
00:23:50,345 --> 00:23:53,056
Uh… Right. Right.

490
00:23:53,849 --> 00:23:57,144
Tutor and tutee seems like a much more
natural relationship between us.

491
00:23:57,894 --> 00:23:58,728
Exactly.

492
00:24:00,188 --> 00:24:04,443
-So, would you maybe want to sign my cast?
-Yeah.

493
00:24:05,235 --> 00:24:06,903
[gentle music playing]

494
00:24:06,987 --> 00:24:08,822
It's pretty crowded.

495
00:24:08,905 --> 00:24:12,617
I see Zoe Maytag wasn't overly concerned
with leaving room for others.

496
00:24:12,701 --> 00:24:16,037
That's Zoe. She actually wrote over,
like, a couple names I think.

497
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,914
I'm not surprised.

498
00:24:25,422 --> 00:24:26,590
Check this out.

499
00:24:27,883 --> 00:24:31,386
A "B." Did Devi have a bad day?

500
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:36,099
No, I had a good day.
I actually studied and got this on my own.

501
00:24:36,808 --> 00:24:38,268
You opened a textbook?

502
00:24:38,894 --> 00:24:41,313
I did. I even read
all the words on the pages.

503
00:24:41,396 --> 00:24:43,106
She taught you how to read?

504
00:24:43,190 --> 00:24:45,066
[Hadid] Yes, Rebecca!

505
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:47,736
Someone get her on Twitter.
We need her realness.

506
00:24:48,945 --> 00:24:52,157
You were right. If I'm going to college,
I want to earn it.

507
00:24:52,782 --> 00:24:53,992
I'm proud of you.

508
00:24:54,618 --> 00:24:56,661
Thanks, Becca. I'm proud of you too.

509
00:24:57,287 --> 00:25:00,373
Hey, could you try these on?

510
00:25:00,457 --> 00:25:03,043
I think you're the same size
as Kendall Jenner.

511
00:25:03,835 --> 00:25:06,338
I think I'm more of a Kylie, but…
[exhales]

512
00:25:07,547 --> 00:25:10,050
[Hadid] Well, this has been a real blast,

513
00:25:10,133 --> 00:25:12,969
but I gotta get
back to my super fulfilling life

514
00:25:13,053 --> 00:25:14,221
as a multi-hyphenate.

515
00:25:15,138 --> 00:25:18,725
I hope we've all learned that
we shouldn't judge a book by its cover,

516
00:25:18,808 --> 00:25:21,686
and that the Cold War ended in 1991.

517
00:25:22,687 --> 00:25:24,689
John McEnroe, back to you.

